This paper focuses on deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for vision tasks, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses compression techniques, which fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could also fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
